	('Volcano', 3, 'Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.'),
	('Big Jaw', 2, 'Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile''s jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.'),
	('Big Jaw', 2, 'Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when the have sunk in.'),
	('Big Jaw', 2, 'Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.'),
	('Scout', 6, 'When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.'),
	('Long Body', 6, 'Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.'),
	('Owl', 6, 'Hoothoot has an internal organ that senses and tracks the earth''s rotation. Using this special organ, this Pokémon begins hooting at precisely the same time every day.'),
	('Owl', 6, 'Noctowl never fails at catching prey in darkness. This Pokémon owes its success to its superior vision that allows it to see in minimal light, and to its soft, supple wings that make no sound in flight.'),
	('Five Star', 1, 'Ledyba secretes an aromatic fluid from where its legs join its body. This fluid is used for communicating with others. This Pokémon conveys its feelings to others by altering the fluid''s scent.'),
	('Five Star', 1, 'It is said that in lands with clean air, where the stars fill the sky, there live Ledian in countless numbers. There is a good reason for this—the Pokémon uses the light of the stars as its energy.'),
	('String Spit', 4, 'The web spun by Spinarak can be considered its second nervous system. It is said that this Pokémon can determine what kind of prey is touching its web just by the tiny vibrations it feels through the web''s strands.'),
	('Long Leg', 1, 'Ariados''s feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. This Pokémon constricts the foe with thin and strong silk webbing.'),
	('Bat', 7, 'If this Pokémon is flying by fluttering only a pair of wings on either the forelegs or hind legs, it''s proof that Crobat has been flying a long distance. It switches the wings it uses if it is tired.'),
	('Angler', 2, 'Chinchou lets loose positive and negative electrical charges from its two antennas to make its prey faint. This Pokémon flashes its electric lights to exchange signals with others.'),
	('Light', 2, 'Lanturn is nicknamed "the deep-sea star" for its illuminated antenna. This Pokémon produces light by causing a chemical reaction between bacteria and its bodily fluids inside the antenna.'),
	('Tiny Mouse', 3, 'Pichu charges itself with electricity more easily on days with thunderclouds or when the air is very dry. You can hear the crackling of static electricity coming off this Pokémon.'),
	('Star Shape', 10, 'On nights with many shooting stars, Cleffa can be seen dancing in a ring. They dance through the night and stop only at the break of day, when these Pokémon quench their thirst with the morning dew.'),
	('Balloon', 10, 'Igglybuff''s vocal cords are not sufficiently developed. It would hurt its throat if it were to sing too much. This Pokémon gargles with freshwater from a clean stream.'),
	('Spike Ball', 9, 'As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon then stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.'),
	('Happiness', 9, 'Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.'),
	('Tiny Bird', 4, 'Natu cannot fly because its wings are not yet fully grown. If your eyes meet with this Pokémon''s eyes, it will stare back intently at you. But if you move even slightly, it will hop away to safety.'),
	('Mystic', 4, 'Xatu stands rooted and still in one spot all day long. People believe that this Pokémon does so out of fear of the terrible things it has foreseen in the future.'),
	('Wool', 9, 'Mareep''s fluffy coat of wool rubs together and builds a static charge. The more static electricity is charged, the more brightly the lightbulb at the tip of its tail glows.'),
	('Wool', 10, 'Flaffy''s wool quality changes so that it can generate a high amount of static electricity with a small amount of wool. The bare and slick parts of its hide are shielded against electricity.'),
	('Light', 3, 'Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.'),
	('Flower', 4, 'When Bellossom gets exposed to plenty of sunlight, the leaves ringing its body begin to spin around. This Pokémon''s dancing is renowned in the southern lands.'),
	('Aqua Mouse', 2, 'Marill''s oil-filled tail acts much like a life preserver. If you see just its tail bobbing on the water''s surface, it''s a sure indication that this Pokémon is diving beneath the water to feed on aquatic plants.'),
	('Aqua Rabbit', 2, 'Azumarill''s long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.'),
	('Imitation', 6, 'Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pokémon is easily identified as a fake during the winter.'),
	('Frog', 4, 'The curled hair on Politoed''s head is proof of its status as a king. It is said that the longer and more curled the hair, the more respect this Pokémon earns from its peers.'),
	('Cottonweed', 10, 'This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.'),
	('Cottonweed', 4, 'Skiploom''s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.'),
	('Cottonweed', 2, 'Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.'),
	('Long Tail', 7, 'Aipom''s tail ends in a hand-like appendage that can be cleverly manipulated. However, because the Pokémon uses its tail so much, its real hands have become rather clumsy.'),
	('Seed', 3, 'Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.'),
	('Sun', 3, 'Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.'),
	('Clear Wing', 1, 'Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.'),
	('Water Fish', 2, 'Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.'),
	('Water Fish', 2, 'Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.'),
	('Sun', 7, 'Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.'),
	('Moonlight', 5, 'Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon''s waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.'),
	('Darkness', 5, 'Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.'),
	('Slowking', 10, 'Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.'),
	('Screech', 8, 'Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.'),
	('Symbol', 5, 'This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.'),
	('Patient', 2, 'If two or more Wobbuffet meet, they will turn competitive and try to outdo each other''s endurance. However, they may try to see which one can endure the longest without food. Trainers need to beware of this habit.'),
	('Long Neck', 3, 'Girafarig''s rear head also has a brain, but it is small. The rear head attacks in response to smells and sounds. Approaching this Pokémon from behind can cause the rear head to suddenly lash out and bite.'),
	('Bagworn', 8, 'Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.'),
	('Bagworm', 7, 'Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell''s inside cannot be seen.'),
	('Land Snake', 3, 'Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.'),
	('Fly Scorpion', 7, 'Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.'),
	('Iron Snake', 8, 'Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth''s core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.'),
	('Fairy', 10, 'By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.'),
	('Fairy', 7, 'Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.'),
	('Balloon', 8, 'Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.'),
	('Pincer', 1, 'Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.'),
	('Mold', 3, 'Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.'),
	('Single Horn', 2, 'Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe''s grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.'),
	('Sharp Claw', 5, 'Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into bark. It seeks out unguarded nests and steals Eggs for food while its parents are away.'),
	('Little Bear', 6, 'This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.'),
	('Hibernator', 6, 'In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.'),